comment:
* Describes a cell-broadcast service. This class should not be instantiated directly -- use
 * {@link StreamingServiceInfo} or {@link FileServiceInfo}

variables.name: MAP_LIMIT
variables.comment: arbitrary limit on the number of locale -> name pairs we support

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(Parcel dest, int flags)
public CharSequence getNameForLocale(@NonNull Locale locale)
methods.comment:
* Get the user-displayable name for this cell-broadcast service corresponding to the
     * provided {@link Locale}.
     * @param locale The {@link Locale} in which you want the name of the service. This must be a
     *               value from the set returned by {@link #getNamedContentLocales()} -- an
     *               {@link java.util.NoSuchElementException} may be thrown otherwise.
     * @return The {@link CharSequence} providing the name of the service in the given
     *         {@link Locale}

methods.name: public Set<Locale> getNamedContentLocales()
methods.comment:
* Return an unmodifiable set of the current {@link Locale}s that have a user-displayable name
     * associated with them. The user-displayable name associated with any {@link Locale} in this
     * set can be retrieved with {@link #getNameForLocale(Locale)}.
     * @return An unmodifiable set of {@link Locale} objects corresponding to a user-displayable
     * content name in that locale.

methods.name: public String getServiceClassName()
methods.comment: * The class name for this service - used to categorize and filter

methods.name: public List<Locale> getLocales()
methods.comment: * The languages available for this service content

methods.name: public String getServiceId()
methods.comment: * The carrier's identifier for the service.

methods.name: public Date getSessionStartTime()
methods.comment: * The start time indicating when this service will be available.

methods.name: public Date getSessionEndTime()
methods.comment: * The end time indicating when this session stops being available.
